  "doc_id": "35422",
  "text": "As mentioned in section 1, EVT-VaR can only be applied to i.id observations, while the foreign exchange data always exhibits property of dependence especially clustering volatility. Hence, [CITATION_1] advise to use GARCH model in the first stage to filter the raw data to be i.id residuals which can then be used in the second stage in 2.1. Additionally, in order to accommodate the possibility of asymmetry or say leverage effect, we will replace the basic symmetric GARCH model with a family of asymmetric GARCH models. [CITATION_2] proposed the exponential GARCH model to account for asymmetric effect:",
